### Decision: How to configure custom SMTP (Resend) and rate limits on Supabase when hitting "email rate limit exc

**Date:** 2026-02-17
**Context:** How to configure custom SMTP (Resend) and rate limits on Supabase when hitting "email rate limit exceeded" errors:
**Decision:** How to configure custom SMTP (Resend) and rate limits on Supabase when hitting "email rate limit exceeded" errors:

## Problem
Default Supabase SMTP has very low rate limits (2-4 emails/hour). OTP/magic link flows hit 429 "over_email_send_rate_limit" quickly during development/testing.

## Solution: Supabase Management API
The Supabase MCP server does NOT have a tool for updating auth config. Use the Management API directly via curl:

```bash
# Get access token from https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
export SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN="sbp_..."
export PROJECT_REF="your-project-ref"

# Configure custom SMTP + rate limits in one PATCH call
curl -s -X PATCH "https://api.supabase.com/v1/projects/$PROJECT_REF/config/auth" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "external_email_enabled": true,
    "smtp_admin_email": "onboarding@resend.dev",
    "smtp_host": "smtp.resend.com",
    "smtp_port": "587",
    "smtp_user": "resend",
    "smtp_pass": "re_YOUR_RESEND_API_KEY",
    "smtp_sender_name": "Your App Name",
    "rate_limit_email_sent": 100,
    "rate_limit_otp": 100
  }'
```

## Verify config was applied
```bash
curl -s "https://api.supabase.com/v1/projects/$PROJECT_REF/config/auth" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN" | jq '{smtp_host, smtp_user, smtp_admin_email, smtp_sender_name, rate_limit_email_sent, rate_limit_otp}'
```

## Key details
- Resend SMTP: host=smtp.resend.com, port=587, user="resend", pass=your Resend API key
- smtp_port must be a string "587" not integer
- Dashboard SMTP settings sometimes don't apply — Management API is more reliable
- Default rate_limit_otp is 30/hr, rate_limit_email_sent is ~2-4/hr on built-in SMTP
- After switching to custom SMTP, default email rate limit starts at 30/hr — set higher explicitly
- Check auth logs for "over_email_send_rate_limit" error_code to confirm rate limiting
- Always rotate access tokens and API keys after using them in terminals/conversations

## Debugging
Check auth logs via Supabase MCP: get_logs(project_id, service: "auth") and grep for "rate_limit" or "smtp"
**Reasoning:** 
**Alternatives:** _email_send_rate_limit" quickly during development/testing.

