### Decision: React 19 pattern: useRef() without arguments causes TS error "Expected 1 arguments, but got 0". Alwa

**Date:** 2026-02-19
**Context:** React 19 pattern: useRef() without arguments causes TS error "Expected 1 arguments, but got 0"
**Decision:** React 19 pattern: useRef() without arguments causes TS error "Expected 1 arguments, but got 0". Always pass explicit initial value: useRef<T>(undefined) or useRef<T>(null). Also, never read localStorage in useState initializers for SSR/hydration safety — always defer to useEffect.
**Reasoning:** 

